[{"question":"Is there some surprise that he hasn\u0027t already taken action and fired those responsible?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a difficult situation over there because the alternative to not knowing was knowing which would have been another headache.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":31,"aSentId":32},{"question":"Mr. Mayor, what is your reaction to Chris Christie\u0027s statement late this afternoon?","answer":"That he\u0027s appalled.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"Do you believe that Chris Christie knew nothing about this as he claims?","answer":"I don\u0027t know.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":47,"aSentId":48},{"question":"It\u0027s hard to imagine a more serious abuse of power, isn\u0027t it Mr. Mayor?","answer":"I would agree, you know.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":71,"aSentId":72},{"question":"Should people be fired, should any of any of these people be in a job by tomorrow morning one to be name in shame today?","answer":"OKOLICH: People that are in these positions of authority that behave this way, that put petty politics ahead of the health safety and welfare of my residents and the residents of the entire state of New Jersey truly can\u0027t be in those positions.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":98,"aSentId":99},{"question":"Have you heard from anybody in Chris Christie\u0027s camp including the governor\u0027s staff?","answer":"No, zero.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":125,"aSentId":126},{"question":"No apology?","answer":"Remain mindful, Piers, I\u0027m not on his radar, so I trust, I\u0027m not in his (inaudible) either.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"What is your reaction to this extraordinary development today which lays clear evidence now that takes right to the heart of Chris Christie\u0027s operation that they did this deliberately?","answer":"Well, I have been involved in this issue for four months which Mayor Sokolich knows.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":136,"aSentId":137},{"question":"-- if I could jump in, should Chris Christie be firing people over this?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":153,"aSentId":154},{"question":"Is it likely that that was ever in their minds?","answer":"Well, if you call the traffic study three or four days beforehand where you have the idea put forward that you\u0027re going to close a few lanes and look at that, I suppose you vaguely could call that a traffic study.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":170,"aSentId":171},{"question":"It was over 30 years that\u0027s been done that way, you know, why not continue?","answer":"Yeah, as you\u0027re talking, John, we\u0027re actually looking pictures from the time back in September where you can see the traffic currents (ph) and everything else.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":176,"aSentId":177},{"question":"How serious could this be for Chris Christie?","answer":"It\u0027s very serious I think it could threaten his presidential ambitions if he is directly tied to this scandal which he hasn\u0027t yet been.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":198,"aSentId":199},{"question":"Do you like the fact that you have this slightly intimidating reputation?","answer":"I don\u0027t like or just like it, it\u0027s just kind of what it is.","docId":"140108pmt","qSentId":245,"aSentId":246}]